snippet.textDisplay: This might be a bit of a random comment but I'd like to recommend some rain boots for you. I work in turkey processing and we wear "safety toed" rain boots. The Tingley Flite series is super lightweight they have the safety toe on them and are incredibly warm as well as comfortable. They have three different treads on them one being specifically for mud and outdoor work. I would HIGHLY recommend these to anyone needing rain boots. They tend to run about a size small in my personal experience so if you wear a 10 pick up a size 11.

snippet.textDisplay:
Great video as usual, love watching the trail building.
Couple suggestions, get a 'Cant Hook' and maybe a 'Peavy' to help move logs. Also a small ratchet strap would help hold logs to your hand truck.
Then make sure your log being milled is blocked up high enough your bar & chain always stay out of the dirt.
Ride free, get stoked.
snippet.textOriginal:
